  • Classes in uk.ac.ebi.pride.jmztab.model used by uk.ac.ebi.pride.jmztab.model 
    Class and Description
    AbundanceColumn.Field 
    Assay
    The application of a measurement about the sample (in this case through MS) - producing values about small molecules, peptides or proteins.
    AssayQuantificationMod
    A parameter describing a modification associated with a quantification_reagent for a assay.
    ColUnit
    Defines the unit for the data reported in a column of the protein, peptide, psm and small molecule section.
    Comment
    Comment lines can be placed anywhere in an mzTab file.
    Contact
    Setting contact name, email, affiliation in Metadata.
    CV
    Define the controlled vocabularies/ontologies used in the mzTab file.
    CVParam
    The PSI-MS controlled vocabulary is intended to provide terms for annotation of mzML, mzIdentML, and mzQuantML files.
    FixedMod
    Fixed Modification used to identify peptides and proteins of the mzTab file (e.g.
    IndexedElement
    Index-organized MetadataElement, index value is positive integer.
    Instrument
    Define a MS instrument.
    Metadata
    The metadata section can provide additional information about the dataset(s) reported in the mzTab file.
    MetadataElement
    Define all elements used in metadata.
    MetadataProperty
    Define a property in metadata, which depend on the MetadataElement or MetadataSubElement
    MetadataSubElement
    A special element which depend on a MetadataElement, the structure like: {element name}[id]-{subElement subName}
    Mod
    Defining modifications in the meta-data section.
    Modification
    Reporting of modifications in columns of the protein, peptide, small molecule and PSM sections.
    Modification.Type 
    MsRun
    An MS run is effectively one run (or set of runs on pre-fractionated samples) on an MS instrument, and is referenced from assay in different contexts.
    MZBoolean
    In mzTab, using 0-false, 1-true to express the boolean value.
    MZTabColumn
    Define a column header which used in Section.Protein_Header, Section.Peptide_Header, Section.PSM_Header, or Section.Small_Molecule_Header.
    MZTabColumnFactory
    This is a static factory class which used to generate a couple of MZTabColumn objects, and organized them "logicalPosition, MZTabColumn" pair.
    MZTabDescription
    Describe all the fields which start with "mzTab-" in metadata section.
    MZTabDescription.Mode 
    MZTabDescription.Type 
    MZTabRecord
    MZTabRecord used to store a row record of the table.
    OptionColumn
    Additional columns can be added to the end of the protein table.
    Param
    mzTab makes use of CV parameters.
    Peptide
    The peptide section is table based.
    PeptideColumn
    Define the stable columns and optional columns which have stable order in peptide header line.
    PeptideSearchEngineScore
    Peptide search engine score cv param used to identify the type of scoring system used in the values of columns like best_search_engine_score and/or search_engine_score in the peptide section.
    Protein
    The protein section is table-based.
    ProteinColumn
    Define the stable columns and optional columns which have stable order in protein header line.
    ProteinSearchEngineScore
    Protein search engine score cv param used to identify the type of scoring system used in the values of columns like best_search_engine_score and/or search_engine_score in the protein section.
    PSM
    The PSM section is table-based.
    PSMColumn
    Define the stable columns and optional columns which have stable order in PSM header line.
    PSMSearchEngineScore
    PSM search engine score cv param used to identify the type of scoring system used in search_engine_score in the PSM section.
    Publication
    A publication associated with this file.
    PublicationItem
    There are two kinds of publication items, PubMed and doi.
    PublicationItem.Type 
    QuantificationReagent
    The reagent used to label the sample in the assay.
    Reliability
    All protein, peptide, psm and small molecule identifications reported in an mzTab file MAY be assigned a reliability score (column "reliability" in all tables).
    Sample
    A biological material that has been analysed, to which descriptors of species, cell/tissue type etc.
    SearchEngineScore
    Search engine score cv param used to identify the type of scoring system used in the values of columns like best_search_engine_score and/or search_engine_score in the different sections.
    Section
    Every line in an mzTab file MUST start with a three letter code identifying the type of line delimited by a Tab character.
    SmallMolecule
    The small molecule section is table-based.
    SmallMoleculeColumn
    Define the stable columns and optional columns which have stable order in small molecule header line.
    SmallMoleculeSearchEngineScore
    Small molecule search engine score cv param used to identify the type of scoring system used in the values of columns like best_search_engine_score and/or search_engine_score in the small molecule section.
    Software
    Software Version used to analyze the data and obtain the results reported.
    SpectraRef
    Peptides and small molecules MAY be linked to the source spectrum (in an external file) from which the identifications are made by way of a reference in the spectra_ref attribute and via the ms_file element which stores the URL of the file in the location attribute.
    SplitList
    This is list which each item split by a split char.
    StudyVariable
    The variables about which the final results of a study are reported, which may have been derived following averaging across a group of replicate measurements (assays).
    VariableMod
    Variable Modification used to identify peptides and proteins of the mzTab file (e.g.
